<br>
Their eyes glittered in the semi darkness as they came into view, their hairy bodies carrying the stench of the sewers that had matted into their fur. I had never met any before but from the rumors I heard they were helping the humans against the vampires. The <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>were</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> creatures were probably the only hope the pathetic humans had anyway.<br>
<br>
&quot;Lost are we?&quot; growled a very large and towering wolf man as he talked right up into my face and stood his full height. &quot;Such a pretty thing down here is a rare sight... you must be looking for something. Be it us or not, you have been found.&quot; his voice was deep as he continued as his eyes traveled all over me. I knew I had to play this one cool so I slowly clicked back my swords and moved my hands away from my guns. I was outnumbered twenty to one from what I could see.<br>
<br>
&quot;Lost? No... I am a vampire hunter and have been tracking one through here that stole away a poor girl and her baby.&quot; I replied in a soft voice as I locked my eyes right up into his steady gaze. &quot;He is a tricky fellow and I can only hope you do not hold me up long so I can free the girl.&quot; my body moved in a slightly seductive manner as I acted with sincerity I did not really have.<br>
<br>
&quot;Vampires... Those pieces of shit!&quot; snapped one of the other <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>were</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> creatures from the shadows. &quot;Always thinking they can do anything.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes... they do don't they... now can I please continue on?&quot; I caused my voice to tremble as I forced myself to place my hand on the leader's greasy fur and stroked it softly. <br>
<br>
His thick hands wrapped around my waist in an instant, holding me tight and I fought my nature to attack my way out. I had to be careful here for these creatures could turn into temporary allies. &quot;We will help you my little lady.&quot; he grinned with sharp teeth as I moved my head so his saliva missed my face and fell with a slimy caress upon the top of my left breast. &quot;But you have come across our territory so for that you must pay us a traveling fee.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Traveling fee?&quot; I leaned back as best I could from his hairy chest. I was beginning to get very uncomfortable with were this was beginning to turn. &quot;I'm a hunter... killing your enemy and you do this to me?&quot; I fought back the urge to snap my fangs at him. <br>
<br>
&quot;Yes I will do as I wish with you for though you kill our sworn enemy, you yourself are not completely human either. So since we hate all things vampire including half vampires, you will treat me to a trick before we help you capture this vampire and we will help you kill him.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Shit this was not what I had in mind at all... I wanted them to help me outta here but they are on to me... Well sorta but what will they do when they find out George is human? Wait a minute this is perfect, he will naturally fight back being the dumb ass that he is and I'll get outta there before these hairy monsters knows it.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I thought to myself as I tried to ignore what I was feeling rising up from between his legs.<br>
