<br>
Slowly I struggled to my feet as the feeling of sickness washed away. I shook my head to free myself of the cobwebs and looked towards a building with steel inforced windows and door. Zabian stood over by the door and I could see them playing with what appeared to be a door code device. I could only trust that I really was at the right place since I had been out for the remainder of the trip here. I knew George had to have some sort of protection about the place if this was really his home but I did not bother warning the others. They were to eager to get the &quot;vampire&quot; to even notice as I snapped my swords into place.<br>
<br>
Thats when the ground shook as a loud explosion and blast came from the building. Before my very eyes I watched Zabian blow apart as the rest of his followers dove for cover behind and scatter like a flock of chickens. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>That couldn't have been more perfect HAHA</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I smirked as I quickly limped towards the door and through the smoke before collapsing onto the floor midst the rubble just inside the building. What I had been through in Zabian's hands had taken a toll on my legs and I could hardly walk but if George was really in here and really wanted to fight, I would go out with a blaze of swords and guns. Of course if he was in here and left me alone, I would be grateful enough to not attack him as previously planned.<br>
